n
\sin\left(\frac{2\pi k}{n}\right)
k = 1,\dots,n-1
0
\sum_{k=0}^{m-1} \sin \frac{2 \pi k}{n}
m = n
\sum_{k=0}^{m-1} \sin \frac{2 \pi k}{n} = \sum_{k=0}^{m-1} \Im(e^{2 \pi ik/n}) = \Im \frac{e^{2 \pi im/n} -1}{e^{2 \pi i/n}-1} 
\sum_{k=0}^{m-1} \sin \frac{2 \pi k}{n} = \Im \frac{e^{2 \pi i} -1}{e^{2 \pi i/n}-1} = \Im \frac{1 -1}{e^{2 \pi i/n}-1} = 0 
